```json
{
  "application": "LAMMPS",
  "details": {
    "software": {
      "lammps": {
        "version": "29Sep2021",
        "mpi": "openmpi-4.0.3_intel2020"
      },
      "kokkos": {
        "version": "3.2.00",
        "compiler": "gcc-7.5.0-dd3pqj3"
      },
      "cuda": {
        "version": "11.5.0",
        "compiler": "gcc-7.5.0-syen6pj"
      },
      "cmake": {
        "version": "3.18.4",
        "compiler": "gcc-7.5.0-mbftn7v"
      },
      "openmpi": {
        "version": "4.1.1",
        "compiler": "gcc-7.5.0-fxaxwiu"
      }
    },
    "resources": {
      "partition": "batch",
      "constraint": "intel",
      "nodes": 1,
      "tasks_per_node": 12,
      "time": "1:00:00",
      "mpi_procs": 12,
      "input_file": "in.reax"
    }
  }
}
```

The script runs a LAMMPS simulation, utilizing different software and resource configurations based on the specified machine environment ("IBEX" or "HPC"). It utilizes modules for loading and managing software dependencies and utilizes SLURM for job submission and resource allocation.
